gobblin.writer.partitioner

Class TimeBasedWriterPartitioner<D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.writer.partitioner.TimeBasedWriterPartitioner<D>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WriterPartitioner<D>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TimeBasedAvroWriterPartitioner

    public abstract class TimeBasedWriterPartitioner<D>
extends java.lang.Object
implements WriterPartitioner<D>
    A WriterPartitioner that partitions a record based on a timestamp. There are two ways to partition a timestamp: (1) specify a DateTimeFormat using WRITER_PARTITION_PATTERN, e.g., 'yyyy/MM/dd/HH'; (2) specify a TimeBasedWriterPartitioner.Granularity using WRITER_PARTITION_GRANULARITY. A prefix and a suffix can be added to the partition, e.g., the partition path can be 'prefix/2015/11/05/suffix'.
